# Premium layout and motion

## Layout

- Clear hierarchy: headline → supporting copy → primary action
- Controlled line lengths for readability; align grids and spacing rhythm across sections
- Photography and overlays should preserve **contrast** for text and buttons

## Motion (Framer Motion, GSAP)

- Motion should **support** content—timing that feels calm and confident
- Hero **scroll-expand** and similar patterns must honor **`prefers-reduced-motion`** with simpler behavior
- GSAP usage should **clean up** (`gsap.context` revert / kill ScrollTriggers on unmount) to avoid leaks and duplicate triggers
- Do not stack competing scroll hijacks without clear UX; prefer one primary interaction model per viewport region

## Performance

- Lazy-load heavy below-the-fold media where practical
- Avoid unnecessary always-on animation loops

See also `design-direction.mdc` and `preserve-existing-work.mdc`.
